1
00:00:29,000 --> 00:00:31,291
You gotta be kidding. Get down!

2
00:00:46,125 --> 00:00:47,458
[GOROBEI] I see it!

3
00:00:54,333 --> 00:00:56,333
[YOHEI]
Serves you right, Bandit!

4
00:00:56,416 --> 00:00:58,875
You'll have to
forgive me, Rikichi...

5
00:00:58,958 --> 00:01:02,500
Looks like I can't take you
to the Capital, after all.

6
00:01:02,583 --> 00:01:04,541
Oh, Great Samurai...

7
00:01:06,375 --> 00:01:09,875
Your life... I have stolen it.

8
00:01:09,958 --> 00:01:13,750
You... gotta be kidding me.

9
00:01:19,000 --> 00:01:24,000
♪ opening song ♪

10
00:02:53,666 --> 00:02:55,791
[BIRD CALLS]

11
00:02:55,875 --> 00:02:58,916
[FARMERS]
♪ Ending season, bending ears, ♪

12
00:02:59,000 --> 00:03:02,833
♪ it's time to
harvest ri-i-ice! ♪

13
00:03:02,916 --> 00:03:06,166
♪ Sharpened reapers,
severed stalks, ♪

14
00:03:06,250 --> 00:03:10,166
♪ for better meals
toni-i-ight! ♪ 

15
00:03:10,250 --> 00:03:13,458
♪ Flung in bundles,
hung in rows, ♪

16
00:03:13,541 --> 00:03:17,333
♪ then ripened by the su-u-un! ♪

17
00:03:17,416 --> 00:03:20,708
♪ On our knees like
honored prayers, ♪

18
00:03:20,791 --> 00:03:24,708
♪ don't slow until
it's do-o-one! ♪ 

19
00:03:24,791 --> 00:03:27,791
♪ Ending season, bending ears, ♪

20
00:03:27,875 --> 00:03:29,125
♪ it's time to... ♪

21
00:03:29,208 --> 00:03:30,583
Finally harvest time?

22
00:03:30,666 --> 00:03:33,833
Yes... And as it should be.

23
00:03:33,916 --> 00:03:39,250
[CHILDREN LAUGH]

24
00:03:39,333 --> 00:03:41,666
[KIKUCHIYO] Hey! What are
you runts laughing at?!

25
00:03:41,750 --> 00:03:44,125
You're just not cut out
for harvesting work, Kiku.

26
00:03:44,208 --> 00:03:45,541
[KIKUCHIYO] Excuse me?

27
00:03:45,625 --> 00:03:47,833
I may look like this now,
but in my farming days,

28
00:03:47,916 --> 00:03:52,916
they called me the "Swift God
of the Rice Field Workers!"

29
00:03:53,000 --> 00:03:53,791
Really?

30
00:03:53,875 --> 00:03:55,708
Long name...
don't you think?

31
00:03:55,791 --> 00:03:58,000
[KIKUCHIYO] It sounded better
when they sang it, okay!

32
00:03:58,083 --> 00:04:00,250
It's not my fault!
These sickles are too small!

33
00:04:00,333 --> 00:04:02,333
It's like I'm cutting rice
with a toothpick!

34
00:04:02,416 --> 00:04:04,583
They're not too small--
you're just too big.

35
00:04:04,666 --> 00:04:05,916
Or too clumsy.

36
00:04:06,000 --> 00:04:06,916
[CHILDREN LAUGH]

37
00:04:07,000 --> 00:04:08,708
[SHINO] Great Samurai.

38
00:04:08,791 --> 00:04:10,958
We'll take it from here, okay?

39
00:04:11,041 --> 00:04:12,375
[KIKUCHIYO] Why?!

40
00:04:12,458 --> 00:04:14,083
We know you were a farmer once,
and that you mean well,

41
00:04:14,166 --> 00:04:16,750
but that body of yours
is only meant for war now--

42
00:04:16,833 --> 00:04:19,375
You're simply not built
for harvesting rice anymore.

43
00:04:19,458 --> 00:04:20,541
Please, Great Samurai,

44
00:04:20,625 --> 00:04:22,000
you've shown your
skills fighting Bandits.

45
00:04:22,083 --> 00:04:23,791
Now let us do
what we're good at.

46
00:04:23,875 --> 00:04:25,708
We've lost so much
harvesting time already

47
00:04:25,791 --> 00:04:26,875
because of the battles.

48
00:04:26,958 --> 00:04:29,208
We just want things
to go smoothly now.

49
00:04:30,875 --> 00:04:32,083
[KIKUCHIYO] Fine.

50
00:04:39,375 --> 00:04:40,416
[KIKUCHIYO]
Hey there, Goro.

51
00:04:40,500 --> 00:04:42,458
You enjoying the sun today?

52
00:04:42,541 --> 00:04:45,541
Heh, heh...
Damn these farmers.

53
00:04:45,625 --> 00:04:49,208
Apparently, I'm useless now.
Just a heap of metal in the way.

54
00:04:49,291 --> 00:04:50,625
I'm restless...

55
00:04:50,708 --> 00:04:53,791
I'm sure you understand,
bein' stuck just lying there...

56
00:04:56,500 --> 00:04:58,375
They're acting
like farmers again.

57
00:04:58,458 --> 00:05:00,458
Worrying about
weather and rice.

58
00:05:00,541 --> 00:05:03,250
Like they've forgotten
all about us, already.

59
00:05:03,333 --> 00:05:05,708
I don't know.
Maybe you died in vain.

60
00:05:05,791 --> 00:05:08,750
That's for Gorobei-sama
to decide, don't you think?

61
00:05:08,833 --> 00:05:10,250
[KIKUCHIYO]
Ahh, it's all just too much!

62
00:05:10,333 --> 00:05:12,416
And what the hell's the
deal with Kambei, huh?!

63
00:05:12,500 --> 00:05:14,666
Bastard up and left and didn't
even take the time to light

64
00:05:14,750 --> 00:05:17,125
a single piece of
incense! Coward!

65
00:05:17,208 --> 00:05:18,291
He and the farmers!

66
00:05:18,375 --> 00:05:20,333
They're all just
a bunch of cowards!

67
00:05:20,416 --> 00:05:22,125
He will be back,
Kikuchiyo.

68
00:05:22,208 --> 00:05:23,583
[KIKUCHIYO]
How can you be sure?!

69
00:05:23,666 --> 00:05:24,708
He'll be back.

70
00:05:24,791 --> 00:05:27,083
He is a samurai,
after all.

71
00:05:30,625 --> 00:05:33,625
[KIKUCHIYO]
Hey. What is a samurai, anyway?

72
00:05:33,708 --> 00:05:35,166
[HEIHACHI]
Look in a mirror...

73
00:05:35,250 --> 00:05:37,708
You'll see one staring back.

74
00:05:39,666 --> 00:05:41,500
[YOHEI] And heave!

75
00:05:41,583 --> 00:05:42,500
[FARMERS] Heave!

76
00:05:42,583 --> 00:05:43,625
[GOSAKU] And pull!

77
00:05:43,708 --> 00:05:47,833
[FARMERS]
Heave ho! Heave ho!

78
00:05:47,916 --> 00:05:56,083
Heave ho! Heave ho!
Heave ho! Heave ho!

79
00:05:56,166 --> 00:06:00,583
[FARMERS MURMUR]

80
00:06:02,291 --> 00:06:04,416
[ELDER] This good
weather helps them work.

81
00:06:04,500 --> 00:06:06,291
[SHICHIROJI]
So does the organization.

82
00:06:06,375 --> 00:06:07,875
You mean these work teams?

83
00:06:07,958 --> 00:06:10,166
That's right. To get ready
for the Nobuseri in time,

84
00:06:10,250 --> 00:06:13,500
we split up all the villagers
into specialized divisions.

85
00:06:13,583 --> 00:06:16,166
The teams were selected based
on each farmer's strengths.

86
00:06:16,250 --> 00:06:17,333
They're working today

87
00:06:17,416 --> 00:06:19,333
in the same teams
they fought yesterday.

88
00:06:19,416 --> 00:06:20,833
And the bonds they
forged during training

89
00:06:20,916 --> 00:06:22,791
are helping them
rebuild quickly.

90
00:06:22,875 --> 00:06:25,000
Combined with Heihachi's
engineering genius,

91
00:06:25,083 --> 00:06:27,166
they probably doubled
their efficiency.

92
00:06:27,250 --> 00:06:32,208
[HEIHACHI]
Pull! Come on! Pull!

93
00:06:32,291 --> 00:06:33,916
[KYUZO] Next.

94
00:06:34,000 --> 00:06:35,708
Draw.

95
00:06:35,791 --> 00:06:37,125
Fire at will.

96
00:06:40,083 --> 00:06:42,916
I wonder if Kambei planned
this from the start...

97
00:06:43,000 --> 00:06:45,000
Keeping you here
to help rebuild.

98
00:06:45,083 --> 00:06:46,666
Sure...

99
00:06:46,750 --> 00:06:49,583
We were hired to save
Kanna from the Bandits...

100
00:06:49,666 --> 00:06:51,541
...and the Bandits
destroyed your homes.

101
00:06:51,625 --> 00:06:53,708
Until you can grow
rice safely again...

102
00:06:53,791 --> 00:06:55,208
...our job's not done.

103
00:07:12,208 --> 00:07:13,416
[DOOR OPENS]

104
00:07:15,291 --> 00:07:16,791
Lady Kirara, I'm sorry.

105
00:07:16,875 --> 00:07:19,750
[KIRARA] You know you don't
have to call me that anymore.

106
00:07:19,833 --> 00:07:21,291
Is that a book about war?

107
00:07:21,375 --> 00:07:22,500
[KATSUSHIRO] Yes...

108
00:07:22,583 --> 00:07:25,250
Since the fighting 
ended, I've felt uneasy.

109
00:07:25,333 --> 00:07:27,958
Like I still crave
the battlefield.

110
00:07:28,041 --> 00:07:32,291
[SOUNDS OF BATTLE]

111
00:07:32,375 --> 00:07:35,083
[KIRARA] In the old age,
war was constant.

112
00:07:35,166 --> 00:07:37,000
As one battle ended,
another began,

113
00:07:37,083 --> 00:07:39,666
and always another
after that...

114
00:07:39,750 --> 00:07:41,083
The battles begat each other,

115
00:07:41,166 --> 00:07:43,083
with power moves
and vows for revenge

116
00:07:43,166 --> 00:07:46,583
calling for each new
season of bloodshed.

117
00:07:46,666 --> 00:07:48,666
War defined the culture,

118
00:07:48,750 --> 00:07:51,458
passing from one
generation to the next.

119
00:07:51,541 --> 00:07:54,833
Every aspect of life revolved
around the preparation, support,

120
00:07:54,916 --> 00:07:57,166
and fighting of war.

121
00:07:57,250 --> 00:07:58,958
For the sake of
victory and survival,

122
00:07:59,041 --> 00:08:01,416
weakness could not be afforded.

123
00:08:01,500 --> 00:08:05,000
To be stronger, the samurai
turned themselves into machines.

124
00:08:05,083 --> 00:08:08,291
The size of their metal bodies
became a symbol of rank.

125
00:08:08,375 --> 00:08:11,500
The bigger they were, the more
authority they possessed.

126
00:08:11,583 --> 00:08:14,250
To be samurai was
no longer an option.

127
00:08:14,333 --> 00:08:16,708
It was the only way to exist.

128
00:08:16,791 --> 00:08:18,333
And the samurai got their wish,

129
00:08:18,416 --> 00:08:21,125
becoming stronger than
any man had dreamed.

130
00:08:21,208 --> 00:08:23,750
But the war would not end.

131
00:08:23,833 --> 00:08:25,791
It brought no good
to the people.

132
00:08:25,875 --> 00:08:27,916
It scorched fields,
crushed houses,

133
00:08:28,000 --> 00:08:31,166
and covered everyone's
faces with ash.

134
00:08:31,250 --> 00:08:33,541
The goals of the war
had been forgotten,

135
00:08:33,625 --> 00:08:34,875
and yet they had to go on,

136
00:08:34,958 --> 00:08:37,875
because without war,
they would have no purpose.

137
00:08:37,958 --> 00:08:40,000
And as long as the
fighting continued,

138
00:08:40,083 --> 00:08:42,625
the samurai would
remain on top.

139
00:08:42,708 --> 00:08:44,958
Every one wanted to be samurai.

140
00:08:45,041 --> 00:08:48,166
Even peasants found their
way into the metal brigades.

141
00:08:48,250 --> 00:08:50,583
But in the end, it was the
samurai's own lust for strength

142
00:08:50,666 --> 00:08:52,458
that enabled their defeat.

143
00:08:52,541 --> 00:08:53,791
The demand for new technologies

144
00:08:53,875 --> 00:08:56,500
created weapons that
could destroy them.

145
00:08:56,583 --> 00:08:59,041
And the weapons were
given to the merchants.

146
00:08:59,125 --> 00:09:01,625
In return, the merchants
used the technology

147
00:09:01,708 --> 00:09:04,500
to rebuild people's
homes, restore cities,

148
00:09:04,583 --> 00:09:08,208
and bring smiles to 
faces blackened with ash.

149
00:09:08,291 --> 00:09:10,875
The Great War was finally over.

150
00:09:10,958 --> 00:09:15,125
The samurai were scattered.
And a new era began.

151
00:09:17,416 --> 00:09:19,958
And now here I am,
a man without purpose...

152
00:09:20,041 --> 00:09:23,166
a samurai in an
age of merchants...

153
00:09:26,166 --> 00:09:28,083
Why did you show
that book to me?

154
00:09:28,166 --> 00:09:30,083
[KIRARA]
I've read it a hundred times.

155
00:09:30,166 --> 00:09:32,166
I know the tragedy
of the samurai.

156
00:09:32,250 --> 00:09:34,250
The impossible
feelings it creates.

157
00:09:34,333 --> 00:09:37,583
Yet I did it to you anyway.
I'm so ashamed.

158
00:09:37,666 --> 00:09:39,166
You can't think that way.

159
00:09:39,250 --> 00:09:43,208
I chose to walk the path of
the Samurai of my own free will.

160
00:09:48,375 --> 00:09:50,416
It's only natural that
the path ahead of me

161
00:09:50,500 --> 00:09:52,583
would be rocky sometimes.

162
00:10:11,875 --> 00:10:14,375
You must take care
of your swords.

163
00:10:14,458 --> 00:10:17,500
I have made the blade
of your daito sharper.

164
00:10:17,583 --> 00:10:20,291
A Samurai is
one who kills.

165
00:10:22,291 --> 00:10:25,083
[KAMBEI] Why did you
come to this village?

166
00:10:25,166 --> 00:10:28,208
To save it, of course.

167
00:10:28,291 --> 00:10:30,458
[KAMBEI]
Then you have done your job.

168
00:10:33,125 --> 00:10:35,833
If you wish to continue
on the Samurai path

169
00:10:35,916 --> 00:10:39,875
you must be prepared to carry
the weight of those you kill.

170
00:10:44,791 --> 00:10:46,500
We are nothing but scarecrows,

171
00:10:46,583 --> 00:10:50,875
driving away the Bandits
who swarm over the crop.

172
00:10:50,958 --> 00:10:53,541
Take your sword
back now, Katsushiro.

173
00:10:55,333 --> 00:10:57,250
Then get yourself some rice...

174
00:10:57,333 --> 00:11:00,000
You'll need your
strength to kill again.

175
00:11:04,958 --> 00:11:06,625
I want to be able to feel proud

176
00:11:06,708 --> 00:11:09,250
that I chose to
become a samurai.

177
00:11:17,000 --> 00:11:18,208
[KAMBEI GASPS]

178
00:11:29,916 --> 00:11:31,291
[KAMBEI] Grab on.

179
00:11:42,750 --> 00:11:45,333
Didn't I tell you
to search elsewhere?

180
00:11:45,416 --> 00:11:46,791
[KIRARA] I knew it.

181
00:11:46,875 --> 00:11:49,375
That why I jumped, because
I knew you would save me.

182
00:11:49,458 --> 00:11:51,208
I know that you're the one.

183
00:11:53,000 --> 00:11:56,916
Your determination and loyalty
have won me over to your cause.

184
00:11:57,000 --> 00:11:58,958
I will help you.

185
00:12:01,583 --> 00:12:05,208
I shall not let your
treasured rice go to waste.

186
00:12:05,291 --> 00:12:06,958
I hardly think I'm worth
a hundred warriors,

187
00:12:07,041 --> 00:12:08,791
but I appreciate the flattery.

188
00:12:08,875 --> 00:12:12,250
Flattery may well be the only
reward you can expect from this.

189
00:12:12,333 --> 00:12:15,416
The only payment we will
receive is the rice we eat.

190
00:12:15,500 --> 00:12:18,166
Hmm...

191
00:12:18,250 --> 00:12:19,708
I accept.

192
00:12:22,875 --> 00:12:24,958
...but at the end of it all
I crawled out of a ship,

193
00:12:25,041 --> 00:12:27,083
covered in soot and
still breathing.

194
00:12:27,166 --> 00:12:28,375
I call it triumph...

195
00:12:28,458 --> 00:12:30,750
If you die, you lose,
if you survive, you win.

196
00:12:30,833 --> 00:12:31,875
It's simple as that.

197
00:12:31,958 --> 00:12:33,708
You really think so?

198
00:12:34,833 --> 00:12:37,541
That's my belief,
for whatever that's worth.

199
00:12:37,625 --> 00:12:39,666
[HEIHACHI]
Much obliged.

200
00:12:39,750 --> 00:12:40,708
[GOROBEI]
Oh by the way,

201
00:12:40,791 --> 00:12:41,833
I don't suppose
you'd be interested

202
00:12:41,916 --> 00:12:43,875
in killing about
forty Nobuseri.

203
00:12:45,958 --> 00:12:47,416
[SHAMISEN MUSIC]

204
00:12:47,500 --> 00:12:54,458
♪ I once cut down bandits
from all three thousand lands. ♪

205
00:12:54,541 --> 00:12:57,625
♪ Cut them down
and got cut down, ♪

206
00:12:57,708 --> 00:13:02,500
♪ but still,
but still I stand. ♪

207
00:13:05,541 --> 00:13:07,500
I'll be at your side.

208
00:13:07,583 --> 00:13:11,041
There's no reward or fame--
only a bloody war. Are you sure?

209
00:13:11,125 --> 00:13:12,583
Yes.

210
00:13:12,666 --> 00:13:15,708
This time we may
meet our deaths.

211
00:13:17,583 --> 00:13:18,708
Sensei, please...

212
00:13:18,791 --> 00:13:20,541
You must continue on
to the village now...

213
00:13:20,625 --> 00:13:23,375
Just go on without me.
I'll only be a burden to you.

214
00:13:23,458 --> 00:13:25,625
Stop acting so
brave, Katsushiro.

215
00:13:25,708 --> 00:13:27,833
I'm not trying to act brave.
I'm serious.

216
00:13:27,916 --> 00:13:30,166
You're frustrated as
anyone would be...

217
00:13:30,250 --> 00:13:32,291
...and that is enough.

218
00:13:33,416 --> 00:13:36,500
These two are grateful
for your sacrifice.

219
00:13:37,541 --> 00:13:40,416
And they should be.

220
00:13:40,500 --> 00:13:42,625
You are their fifth samurai.

221
00:13:42,708 --> 00:13:44,916
Why... Kyuzo...?

222
00:13:45,000 --> 00:13:46,833
Why did you...

223
00:13:49,166 --> 00:13:52,125
Because... I wanted to live.

224
00:13:53,875 --> 00:13:55,666
Hopeless fool.

225
00:13:55,750 --> 00:13:57,666
May I ask you to
come with us?

226
00:13:57,750 --> 00:13:58,958
When do we leave?

227
00:13:59,041 --> 00:14:00,875
Immediately.

228
00:14:00,958 --> 00:14:02,375
[KIKUCHIYO]
I can't blame Manzo,

229
00:14:02,458 --> 00:14:04,375
conniving and
pathetic as he is!

230
00:14:04,458 --> 00:14:07,500
He just played the odds and
the Bandits won! That's all!

231
00:14:07,583 --> 00:14:08,958
Farmers are corrupt!

232
00:14:09,041 --> 00:14:12,791
But Bandits are corrupt!
And Samurai are corrupt!

233
00:14:12,875 --> 00:14:15,500
Why would anyone risk
their lives for anyone?

234
00:14:15,583 --> 00:14:17,000
But I'll fight for them.

235
00:14:17,083 --> 00:14:19,416
I'll kill all
the Bandits! Damn it.

236
00:14:19,500 --> 00:14:22,958
[KIKUCHIYO SOBS]

237
00:14:23,041 --> 00:14:24,375
Damn it...

238
00:14:28,125 --> 00:14:30,750
At last the seven are complete.

239
00:14:32,500 --> 00:14:34,458
This uneasiness I feel...

240
00:14:34,541 --> 00:14:36,666
I think I'm finally
beginning to understand

241
00:14:36,750 --> 00:14:40,500
what Kyuzo-dono meant, when
he said that he wanted to live.

242
00:14:42,208 --> 00:14:44,250
Katsushiro.

243
00:15:07,500 --> 00:15:10,708
[UKYO] So, Kanna Village fought
off those dreadful machines?

244
00:15:10,791 --> 00:15:12,458
Nicely done Kirara darling.

245
00:15:12,541 --> 00:15:14,208
[TESSAI]
With all respect, young master,

246
00:15:14,291 --> 00:15:16,625
the samurai are the ones
responsible for this,

247
00:15:16,708 --> 00:15:18,416
not those peasants.

248
00:15:18,500 --> 00:15:19,666
[UKYO] Ah yes,

249
00:15:19,750 --> 00:15:22,416
but it was Kirara who
assembled those Samurai.

250
00:15:22,500 --> 00:15:25,250
She obviously has a talent
for choosing good men.

251
00:15:25,333 --> 00:15:26,625
[TESSAI]
I've done some more digging.

252
00:15:26,708 --> 00:15:27,958
According to our informants,

253
00:15:28,041 --> 00:15:30,583
the samurai's leader
is named Kambei.

254
00:15:30,666 --> 00:15:32,083
[UKYO]
Who cares what his name is?

255
00:15:32,166 --> 00:15:34,375
The point of the matter is
that a simple farming village

256
00:15:34,458 --> 00:15:37,833
hired samurai and
defeated the bandits.

257
00:15:37,916 --> 00:15:38,958
[TESSAI] Yes.

258
00:15:39,041 --> 00:15:40,000
One more thing...

259
00:15:40,083 --> 00:15:42,666
Tell the other
villages, will you?

260
00:15:43,666 --> 00:15:47,250
Make clear to all farmers.
They have nothing left to fear.

261
00:15:47,333 --> 00:15:49,666
From the bandits... or me.

262
00:15:49,750 --> 00:15:53,250
But... won't that
disrupt the order?

263
00:15:54,666 --> 00:15:55,958
[UKYO]
Just do it, Tessai.

264
00:15:56,041 --> 00:15:58,166
I'm far too busy to be
explaining things to you.

265
00:15:58,250 --> 00:15:59,416
[TESSAI]
As you wish.

266
00:15:59,500 --> 00:16:00,666
[MESSENGER]
Young master...

267
00:16:00,750 --> 00:16:02,291
An urgent message
from the capital.

268
00:16:02,375 --> 00:16:04,625
Oh, then please, do tell.

269
00:16:06,541 --> 00:16:08,875
[MESSENGER] For his inability
to find the envoy's assassin,

270
00:16:08,958 --> 00:16:11,083
Ayamaro has been
stripped of his title.

271
00:16:11,166 --> 00:16:12,208
He will remain in the capital

272
00:16:12,291 --> 00:16:14,333
until the Emperor
decides his fate.

273
00:16:14,416 --> 00:16:16,958
His fate?

274
00:16:17,041 --> 00:16:19,666
Poor Father,
whatever shall we do?

275
00:16:19,750 --> 00:16:21,041
[MESSENGER]
The Emperor would like you

276
00:16:21,125 --> 00:16:24,125
to continue your father's
duties as Magistrate,

277
00:16:24,208 --> 00:16:25,875
Well, that makes sense...

278
00:16:25,958 --> 00:16:28,958
I can't say I want the job,
but who else is there?

279
00:16:29,041 --> 00:16:30,208
[TESSAI SIGHS]

280
00:16:37,083 --> 00:16:38,791
Your tanto--let me have it.

281
00:16:38,875 --> 00:16:39,958
[TESSAI] Huh?

282
00:16:40,041 --> 00:16:41,708
You heard me.
Give me your short blade!

283
00:16:41,791 --> 00:16:44,875
[TESSAI] Yes, young
master, of course.

284
00:16:50,416 --> 00:16:54,791
[CLANGING]

285
00:16:54,875 --> 00:16:56,875
[FACTORY WORKERS MURMUR]

286
00:17:01,416 --> 00:17:02,958
[UKYO]
Hello. Workers!

287
00:17:03,041 --> 00:17:04,791
This is your magistrate!

288
00:17:04,875 --> 00:17:08,125
I know this is a wretched place,
and I'm sorry to keep you here!

289
00:17:08,208 --> 00:17:11,583
But I promise very soon
you will all be free!

290
00:17:20,250 --> 00:17:23,583
Um, Kiku? You do know you
caught something, right?

291
00:17:23,666 --> 00:17:24,791
[KIKUCHIYO] What...?

292
00:17:27,625 --> 00:17:31,416
Look in a mirror...
You'll see one staring back.

293
00:17:32,958 --> 00:17:36,041
Hey sidekick, what's wrong?
I've never seen you this quiet.

294
00:17:36,125 --> 00:17:38,041
[KIKUCHIYO]
What do you think a samurai is?

295
00:17:38,125 --> 00:17:41,583
Somebody like you, you goof.

296
00:17:41,666 --> 00:17:42,875
[KIKUCHIYO] Huh...?

297
00:17:45,041 --> 00:17:47,625
[KOMACHI] Kiku's feeling
kinda lonely now.

298
00:17:47,708 --> 00:17:48,708
[OKARA] How come?

299
00:17:48,791 --> 00:17:50,333
[KOMACHI]
'Cause Kambei isn't here.

300
00:17:50,416 --> 00:17:52,250
[OKARA]
Oh yeah. That makes sense.

301
00:17:52,333 --> 00:17:53,541
[KIKUCHIYO] Shut up!

302
00:17:53,625 --> 00:17:54,958
[KOMACHI] Kiku acts
like he doesn't like him,

303
00:17:55,041 --> 00:17:57,416
but he's followed
Kambei from the start.

304
00:17:57,500 --> 00:17:59,791
You don't recognize me?
I'm not surprised.

305
00:17:59,875 --> 00:18:02,416
The name's Zaemon
Yoshichika the Peaceable.

306
00:18:02,500 --> 00:18:05,416
I was only a boy when
you killed my parents.

307
00:18:05,500 --> 00:18:07,541
I've devoted my life
to their vengeance--

308
00:18:07,625 --> 00:18:09,833
and though I wasn't
expecting to find you today,

309
00:18:09,916 --> 00:18:12,125
it's an opportunity
I won't turn down.

310
00:18:12,208 --> 00:18:14,083
[KIKUCHIYO]
What are you talking about?

311
00:18:14,166 --> 00:18:15,125
Wait!

312
00:18:18,375 --> 00:18:21,000
You saved the girl so you
must be worth something.

313
00:18:21,083 --> 00:18:23,458
Or is that what you
call a losing battle?

314
00:18:23,541 --> 00:18:25,791
Oh, they suffer for you
and you still won't help?!

315
00:18:25,875 --> 00:18:27,458
I'll kill you right here!

316
00:18:27,541 --> 00:18:30,291
[KAMBEI] On my signal,
reel this in as hard as you can.

317
00:18:30,375 --> 00:18:31,708
[KIKUCHIYO] Okay...

318
00:18:31,791 --> 00:18:33,541
Don't have a clue what
you're doing, but you got it!

319
00:18:33,625 --> 00:18:34,500
[GOROBEI] Come on!

320
00:18:34,583 --> 00:18:36,333
Kikuchiyo!

321
00:18:36,416 --> 00:18:38,208
[KIKUCHIYO YELLS]

322
00:18:38,291 --> 00:18:40,333
[KIKUCHIYO]
You better not screw this up!

323
00:18:40,416 --> 00:18:42,583
Save those farmers, okay!

324
00:18:42,666 --> 00:18:45,833
You were born a farmer...
Weren't you, Kikuchiyo?

325
00:18:47,000 --> 00:18:49,000
[KIKUCHIYO]
Okay, I was a farmer, so what!

326
00:18:49,083 --> 00:18:50,333
I figured if I acted
like a samurai,

327
00:18:50,416 --> 00:18:52,916
people would think
of me better!

328
00:18:53,000 --> 00:18:54,583
I want a good battle.

329
00:18:54,666 --> 00:18:57,000
Right. You can count on that.

330
00:18:58,791 --> 00:19:01,166
[OKARA] Kambei's fighting
a one-man war now.

331
00:19:01,250 --> 00:19:03,083
He's not letting the
other samurai help.

332
00:19:03,166 --> 00:19:04,416
[KOMACHI] Yeah.

333
00:19:04,500 --> 00:19:06,916
Momotaro and Heihachi are
busy rebuilding stuff.

334
00:19:07,000 --> 00:19:08,750
But everyone else
is just bored.

335
00:19:08,833 --> 00:19:11,583
[OKARA] Everyone else has
other interests, at least.

336
00:19:11,666 --> 00:19:13,750
Farming's the only
other thing Kiku knows,

337
00:19:13,833 --> 00:19:15,125
but he's no good at it now.

338
00:19:15,208 --> 00:19:18,208
[KOMACHI] Still, they
shouldn't just replace him.

339
00:19:18,291 --> 00:19:21,250
Aah! What are you doing
you dumb fish?

340
00:19:21,333 --> 00:19:23,416
[KIKUCHIYO]
Oh, enough already, okay!

341
00:19:23,500 --> 00:19:25,375
I'm a samurai, damn it!

342
00:19:25,458 --> 00:19:28,375
Now it's time for me to
start acting like one!

343
00:19:28,458 --> 00:19:31,458
[RIKICHI] At least it
would stop the shame...

344
00:19:31,541 --> 00:19:33,541
I sold my wife!

345
00:19:33,625 --> 00:19:35,833
I sold my wife to the Bandits!

346
00:19:35,916 --> 00:19:36,833
What?

347
00:19:36,916 --> 00:19:38,291
[KIKUCHIYO] Rikichi...

348
00:19:38,375 --> 00:19:41,000
[RIKICHI SOBS]

349
00:19:41,083 --> 00:19:42,291
[KAMBEI] Rikichi...

350
00:19:42,375 --> 00:19:45,416
Tell me now, what is
your wife's name?

351
00:19:45,500 --> 00:19:46,833
It's Sanai.

352
00:19:46,916 --> 00:19:49,208
Then I promise
you now, Rikichi...

353
00:19:49,291 --> 00:19:52,416
I will swear to you...
We will save Sanai.

354
00:19:52,500 --> 00:19:53,791
But why...?

355
00:19:53,875 --> 00:19:56,125
That story about your family
being killed by bandits,

356
00:19:56,208 --> 00:19:57,291
was that all a lie?

357
00:19:57,375 --> 00:19:59,583
No, it was all true... Except...

358
00:19:59,666 --> 00:20:01,333
Except what?

359
00:20:01,416 --> 00:20:03,833
My sister... My little sis--

360
00:20:03,916 --> 00:20:05,500
[HONOKA SOBS]

361
00:20:05,583 --> 00:20:07,750
I swear, Lady Honoka,

362
00:20:07,833 --> 00:20:10,291
we will reunite
you and your sister.

363
00:20:12,416 --> 00:20:14,041
[KATSUSHIRO] But why would
he just leave like this,

364
00:20:14,125 --> 00:20:15,791
without asking for our help?

365
00:20:15,875 --> 00:20:18,666
Especially if he's gone to
the Capital, like we think.

366
00:20:18,750 --> 00:20:22,125
He won't be able to get
past their defenses alone.

367
00:20:22,208 --> 00:20:25,000
[KIRARA] Kambei has
more wisdom than us all.

368
00:20:25,083 --> 00:20:27,750
He wouldn't do anything
unless he had a good plan.

369
00:20:27,833 --> 00:20:29,458
The Priestess is
right about that...

370
00:20:29,541 --> 00:20:31,291
And Kyuzo must have
had a plan of his own,

371
00:20:31,375 --> 00:20:33,583
because he's
disappeared as well.

372
00:20:33,666 --> 00:20:34,625
I'm not surprised.

373
00:20:34,708 --> 00:20:35,916
The whole reason he came here

374
00:20:36,000 --> 00:20:38,250
was to battle sensei
after we won...

375
00:20:38,333 --> 00:20:40,333
With sensei gone
there's no challenge...

376
00:20:40,416 --> 00:20:42,750
...and no reason to stay.

377
00:20:42,833 --> 00:20:45,416
That does
sound like Kyuzo.

378
00:20:45,500 --> 00:20:46,833
The rice is safe,

379
00:20:46,916 --> 00:20:49,875
but the seven kami protecting
it have been separated.

380
00:20:49,958 --> 00:20:51,041
Kami?

381
00:20:51,125 --> 00:20:53,666
Oh yeah...
I'd almost forgotten that.

382
00:20:53,750 --> 00:20:54,875
Speaking of old traditions,

383
00:20:54,958 --> 00:20:56,166
have you folks heard
the one that says that

384
00:20:56,250 --> 00:20:58,166
rice contains seven kami?

385
00:20:58,250 --> 00:21:00,875
Kami...?
Like deities?

386
00:21:00,958 --> 00:21:02,458
That's right.

387
00:21:02,541 --> 00:21:04,583
Seven deities who live inside of
good rice grains and protect it.

388
00:21:04,666 --> 00:21:06,000
How can I not love the stuff?

389
00:21:06,083 --> 00:21:08,500
It's a gift blessed
from the heavens!

390
00:21:10,250 --> 00:21:12,541
[KIKUCHIYO]
Hey! Rikichi!

391
00:21:14,958 --> 00:21:16,208
I'm getting out of here!

392
00:21:16,291 --> 00:21:20,208
Can't let that mule
Kambei hog all the glory.

393
00:21:20,291 --> 00:21:21,625
What are you talking about?

394
00:21:21,708 --> 00:21:24,333
Wait a minute, you're
going off to help rescue Sanai?

395
00:21:24,416 --> 00:21:26,333
But Sensei left us
here for a reason.

396
00:21:26,416 --> 00:21:28,333
We need to help
protect the village.

397
00:21:28,416 --> 00:21:30,125
[KIKUCHIYO]
Decision time, kid!

398
00:21:30,208 --> 00:21:33,208
Samurai or sheep--which are you?

399
00:21:33,291 --> 00:21:35,666
Then you're a... samurai?

400
00:21:35,750 --> 00:21:37,416
I'm samurai.

401
00:21:37,500 --> 00:21:40,666
[KIKUCHIYO] That's right!
And it's time to step up!

402
00:21:40,750 --> 00:21:42,333
Kambei may treat
us like children,

403
00:21:42,416 --> 00:21:45,958
but you know in your heart
what a true samurai would do.

404
00:21:46,041 --> 00:21:47,583
We have an opportunity--

405
00:21:47,666 --> 00:21:50,750
no, an obligation to
find Rikichi's wife.

406
00:21:50,833 --> 00:21:52,291
We can do it!

407
00:21:52,375 --> 00:21:55,291
And we can show up that crusty
old jerk while we're at it.

408
00:21:55,375 --> 00:21:58,583
Come on, I know you're
itching for a good fight.

409
00:22:03,416 --> 00:22:08,375
[WIND BLOWS HEAVILY]

410
00:22:29,208 --> 00:22:31,625
Great Samurai, you're back!

411
00:22:33,666 --> 00:22:35,375
But what about
the rest of them?

412
00:22:35,458 --> 00:22:40,083
Katsushiro, and Rikichi...
and Gorobei--are they safe?

413
00:22:40,166 --> 00:22:42,458
[KAMBEI]
Gorobei is dead.

414
00:22:45,458 --> 00:22:49,250
I see... Then what
about Kanna Village?

415
00:22:49,333 --> 00:22:51,958
[KAMBEI]
The Nobuseri were defeated.

416
00:22:52,041 --> 00:22:55,375
I have come to
fulfill my promise.

417
00:22:55,458 --> 00:22:58,291
Rikichi's wife and your sister
are likely in the Capital.

418
00:22:58,375 --> 00:23:00,375
That's where your
masters will take me.

419
00:23:00,458 --> 00:23:01,916
The Capital?

420
00:23:02,000 --> 00:23:03,625
[HONOKA GASPS]

421
00:23:13,458 --> 00:23:18,416
♪ closing song ♪

422
00:25:21,625 --> 00:25:23,708
[OKARA SNICKERS]

423
00:25:23,791 --> 00:25:26,125
[OKARA] Well, the Bandits
are gone and we're still alive.

424
00:25:26,208 --> 00:25:28,958
And I thought we'd all
end up in the ground.

425
00:25:29,041 --> 00:25:30,250
But with the fighting done,

426
00:25:30,333 --> 00:25:32,708
and Kambei off on his own
for whatever reason,

427
00:25:32,791 --> 00:25:35,333
and Momotaro and
Heihachi fixing the village,

428
00:25:35,416 --> 00:25:38,083
that left the other two
pretty much useless.

429
00:25:38,166 --> 00:25:39,958
And just watching them
mope around, I knew it

430
00:25:40,041 --> 00:25:43,916
wouldn't be long before they
wanted to do something crazy.

431
00:25:44,000 --> 00:25:45,375
I guess when you're
used to fighting those

432
00:25:45,458 --> 00:25:48,416
big crimson spiders--which
are super scary by the way--

433
00:25:48,500 --> 00:25:50,875
and having swords at
your throat all the time,

434
00:25:50,958 --> 00:25:53,791
taking a nice day to relax
just isn't quite the same.

435
00:25:53,875 --> 00:25:56,083
Kiku was funny trying
to harvest, though.

436
00:25:56,166 --> 00:25:57,916
I love saying things
to make him angry, 

437
00:25:58,000 --> 00:26:00,000
'cause he starts screaming
and flailing his arms,

438
00:26:00,083 --> 00:26:02,791
and he's like a big monkey,
It's hilarious...

439
00:26:02,875 --> 00:26:05,000
Of course, he can make
you nervous, too,

440
00:26:05,083 --> 00:26:07,750
when he's in your face, and it
does get him what he wants,

441
00:26:07,833 --> 00:26:10,833
'cause now Katsu's going on
some big adventure with him.

442
00:26:10,916 --> 00:26:12,750
I should learn how
to yell like that...

443
00:26:12,833 --> 00:26:18,083
Komachi! Give me your rice!
Give me your rice, you mule!

444
00:26:18,166 --> 00:26:19,625
[OKARA SNICKERS]

